<br>
#1: &quot;You are now hidden!&quot;  See above.<br>
#2: The only timer is for the time between combat and when you can restealth, which is 10 seconds.  You may remain stealthed as long as you wish.<br>
#3: I don't know what F5 defaults to, it's mapped different for me.  Ground target?  That works with Distraction.<br>
#4: Higher Stealth will increase your movement speed slightly while Stealthed, decrease your &quot;You are too close to an enemy to hide!&quot; radius, and make you generally harder to detect.  Read the FAQ.<br>
#5: You may want to head on over to the Ranger's Glade, though I don't have the URL.  Archers frequently run into hostility here <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~bdemong/valarauco.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse>The Safehouse</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22>Stealth Training</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.thesafehouse.org">The Safehouse website</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.guildboss.com"><img
